      \end{flalign*}
      If the investor chooses to risk only a fraction $k_f$ of wealth, then the wealth after the gamble is either $1 + k_f a$ (with probability $p$), or $1 - k_f b$ (with probability $q = 1-p$).
      \vskip1ex
